ly summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_7lLTnuHloB1zOUrRUVLJruG2", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the `methylKit` package in R to handle methylation data.\\n2. Read the `methylRawList` object from `input/mk_raw.rds` using `readRDS`.\\n3. Apply the `filterByCoverage` function with `lo.count=3` and `hi.perc=99.9` to filter the data.\\n4. Normalize the coverage using the `normalizeCoverage` function with the method set to 'median'.\\n5. Save the normalized `methylRawList` object to `output/mk_filt_norm.rds` using `saveRDS`.\\n6. Calculate per-sample statistics: number of CpGs, mean methylation percentage, mean coverage, and median coverage.\\n7. Write these statistics to `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` in TSV format.\\n8. Verify the existence of `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `methylkit_filt_norm`\n\n# Real R-task: methylkit_filt_norm\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `fritjoflammers-snakemake-methylanalysis-finish` (family: `methylation`, stage: `mid`, difficulty: `2`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for of