function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the `methylKit` package in R to handle methylation data.\\n2. Read the `methylRawList` object from `input/mk_raw.rds` using `readRDS`.\\n3. Apply the `filterByCoverage` function with `lo.count=3` and `hi.perc=99.9` to filter the data.\\n4. Normalize the coverage using the `normalizeCoverage` function with the method set to 'median'.\\n5. Save the normalized `methylRawList` object to `output/mk_filt_norm.rds` using `saveRDS`.\\n6. Calculate per-sample statistics: number of CpGs, mean methylation percentage, mean coverage, and median coverage.\\n7. Write these statistics to `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` in TSV format.\\n8. Verify the existence of `output/filt_norm_stats.tsv` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (725 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_7lLTnuHloB1zOUrRUVLJruG2"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_UVMcSxvb1WOS01cZ4UDbrNIo", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\nmk_raw <- readRDS('input/mk_raw.rds')\\nmk_filt <- filterByCoverage(mk_raw, lo.count=3, hi.perc=99.9)\\nmk_norm <- normalizeCoverage(mk_filt, method='median')\\nsaveRDS(mk_norm, 'output/mk_filt_norm.rds')\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=0\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nLoading required package: GenomicRanges\nLoading required package: stats4\nLoading required package: BiocGenerics\nLoading required package: generics\n\nAttaching package: \u2018generics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    as.difftime, as.factor, as.ordered, intersect, is.element, setdiff,\n    setequal, union\n\n\nAttaching package: \u2018BiocGenerics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    IQR, mad, sd, var, xtabs\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    anyDuplicated, aperm, append, as.data.frame, basename, cbind,\n    colnames, dirname, do.call, duplicated, eval, evalq, Filter, Find,\n    get, grep, grepl, is.unsorted, lapply, Map, mapply, match, mget,\n    order, paste, pmax, pmax.int, pmin, pmin.int, Position, rank,\n    rbind, Reduce, rownames, sapply, saveRDS, table, tapply, unique,\n    unsplit, which.max, which.min\n\nLoading required package: S4Vectors\n\nAttaching package: \u2018S4Vectors\u2019\n\nThe following object is masked from \u2018package:utils\u2019:\n\n    findMatches\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    expand.grid, I, unname\n\nLoading required package: IRanges\nLoading required package: GenomeInfoDb\n", "name": "run_rscript", "tool_call_id": "call_UVMcSxvb1WOS01cZ4UDbrNIo"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_6DFa9j5iJwIRiOE4cPa5o2Rp", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"# Calculate per-sample statistics and write to TSV\\nmk_norm <- readRDS('output/mk_filt_norm.rds')\\n\\n# Function to calculate statistics for each sample\\ncalc_stats <- function(methylObj) {\\n  n_CpGs <- length(methylObj)\\n  mean_mCpG <- mean(methylObj$percMethylation)\\n  mean_coverage <- mean(methylObj$coverage)\\n  median_coverage <- median(methylObj$coverage)\\n  return(c(n_CpGs, mean_mCpG, mean_coverage, median_coverage))\\n}\\n\\n# Apply the function to each sample in the methylRawList\\nstats_list <- lapply(mk_norm, calc_stats)\\n\\n# Convert the list to a data frame\\nstats_df <- do.call(rbind, stats_list)\\ncolnames(stats_df) <- c('n_CpGs', 'mean_mCpG', 'mean_coverage', 'median_coverage')\\n\\n# Add sample names\\nstats_df <- data.frame(sample = names(mk_norm), stats_df)\\n\\n# Write to TSV\\nwrite.table(stats_df, 'output/filt_norm_stats.tsv', sep='\\\\t', row.names=FALSE)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, 